result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Robert F. Bradach was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Robert F. Bradach in court with attorney Maris Rushevics. Defendant Robert F. Bradach in custody. David R. Knaapen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

10:05 AM Court calls case.
This is on a review on a revocation of huber.
Atty Knaapen states appearances.

Atty Rushevics addresses the Court, regarding a request of review of huber law priviledges.
Defendant addresses the Court.

Defendant provides  a copy of a letter that he wrote to the Jail, first seen by State, then given to Judge to read. 

State takes no position at this time.

Court addresses the parties.

BY THE COURT:
Court upholds the revocation of the 30 days.  Sheriff's decision to revoke the huber will stand.

Defendant has approximately a week left.

Defendant Robert F. Bradach in court with attorney Maris Rushevics. David R. Knaapen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
8:40 a.m. Court calls the case. 

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of:  Count 1 - NO CONTEST

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Atty Rushevics makes statements re: proposed fine. 
Court questions Atty Knaapen. 
Atty Knaapen makes statements to the Court. 
Atty Rushevics makes additional statements to the Court. 
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty Count 1.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.
Count 2 is dismissed. 

Atty Knaapen makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Rushevics makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 

Court addresses a refusal hearing in 15TR1540.  That is a Village of Plover matter and will not be addressed today. 
Atty Rushevics makes statements to the Court. 
Defendant makes statements to the Court. 
Court questions parties re: statute re: jail sentence commencement. 
Atty Knaapen makes statements to the Court. 

BY THE COURT:
4 years prison with 2 years initial confinement followed by 2 years extended supervision STAYED
Not eligible for Challenge Incarceration but eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
Terms of extended supervision are the same as the conditions of probation. 
Placed on probation for a period of 24 months: 
Pay fine of $2,000 plus costs totaling $3,543.00. 
Pay $33.33 blood draw fee. 
Serve 365 days jail. 
2 days credit which can be credited towards the conditional jail time. 
Huber for work, counseling and any other reason the sheriff will allow. 
Eligible for Electronic Monitoring program after he has served half of that time and after an assessment is done. 
Sentence to commence within 60 days. 
Must report today for start date. 
Obtain AODA and comply with treatment recommendations. 
Maintain absolute sobriety with regard to alcohol. 
Do not operate a vehicle with any alcohol whatsoever in his system. 
Comply with any other assessments or counseling deemed appropriate by his agent.
Revocation for 36 months. 
IID for 36 months. 
DOT Assessment and comply with the safety plan in order to be re-instated. 
Any cash bond posted be applied to fines/costs.  Any remainder be returned to the poster. 
Provide a DNA sample. 


Court provides the defendant with the written explanation of determinate sentence.

$2,500 cash bond (already posted):   Do not possess or consume alcohol or be on premises where alcohol is served/sold as its primary business except within scope of your employment.  Do not operate Motor Vehicle without a valid Drivers License and be absolutely sober.   Participate in the Portage County Pre-Trial Supervision Program and comply with the requirements for reporting, assessment, and programming.
***Stip&Order 12-14-15: Amended that the defendant shall be excused from Day Report obligations on December 24 & 25, 2015 to allow him to attend a family gathering in St Louis over Christmas./s/TBE***
